#X text 74 394 The = variable (not an equals sign) fetches the float
from the pattern toggles. This makes it especially easy to compose
melodies using the GUI friendly toggle floats. Note that only negative
floats will be fetched by messages like this \; positive ones are used
for connections and won't register in the messages. The negative ones
aren't really negative--the absolute value is taken. The negative is
just a way of distinguisging them from the positive. To select a toggle
float \, double click and scroll up or down.;
#X text 73 522 The # variable turns a number into a note. This is defined
by the [scaler] object \, which communicates with all Contexts. You
can change the arguments of [scaler] to change the scale.;
